27/12/2010
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Four Turkish engineers and their local driver were abducted in eastern Afghanistan on Sunday (December 26th) in the Paktia province. 
They were on their way from a building site in the Dand Wa Patan district bordering Pakistan. 
An operation is under way to find the hostages. 
No group has claimed responsibility yet. 
(AFP, BBC, Radikal, Haber Turk, Sabah - 26/12/10)
